<paragraph id="E8A22874B85751CC7F7F67EBA42F3746" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="4087098B3D6710B3D5D2347B098B9F2D" LSID="530C0A57-FE8F-F7AA-02DE-5ACC24FD7137" authority="Puthz, 1972" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus bicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">Stenus bicornis Puthz, 1972</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation id="7718EBB68ABD0843B96CD451FACDEF86" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 7. Stenus circularis species group: ○ Stenus planifrons robustus; 8. Stenus clavicornis species group: ○ Stenus caspius, ● Stenus providus providus; 9. Stenus comma species group: ■ Stenus aereus, ○ Stenus asiaticus, ● Stenus bicornis, ▲ Stenus biguttatus, □ Stenus comma comma; 10. Stenus cordatus species group: ○ Stenus araxis, ● Stenus turk; 11. Stenus crassus and Stenus fornicatus species groups: ■ Stenus crassus, △ Stenus formicetorum, ○ Stenus fornicatus; 12. Stenus glacialis species group: ➕ Stenus armeniacus, ▲ Stenus hospes, ■ Stenus limicola, ○ Stenus medus, ▲ Stenus parcior, □ Stenus persicus, ● Stenus schah." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74429" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
, Suppl. material 1
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72F73AF74831339939737E0CE250F472" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="chorology">
<paragraph id="F6C90D37639DDFF7C2029245F69E213B" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<pageBreakToken id="BCC5BC92DAF74D419B32026F694BF5E1" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" start="start">Chorology</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5075607EF008D9137C09365E7D3F74B7" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Described from Macedonia and Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="EE74D145E856058AC0C22BAC1C8EE107" author="Puthz, V" journalOrPublisher="Wissenschaftliche Mitteilungen des Bosnisch-herzeoginischen Landesmuseums" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="167 - 179" refId="B51" refString="Puthz, V, 1972c. Zur Staphylinidenfauna des Balkans: die bisher aus Jogoslawien und angrenzenden Laendern bekannten Steninen (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Wissenschaftliche Mitteilungen des Bosnisch-herzeoginischen Landesmuseums 2 (c): 167 - 179" title="Zur Staphylinidenfauna des Balkans: die bisher aus Jogoslawien und angrenzenden Laendern bekannten Steninen (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae)." volume="2" year="1972 c">Puthz 1972c</bibRefCitation>
: 170), 
<taxonomicName id="B504DCE7AE10BA46E24350931F276543" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus bicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="9BFD840110827EAF8637FF25F1F70A8A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Stenus bicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the Balkans and Anatolia. The recent records in the very northwest of Iran (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="10A8789FAA98FBAEB7D188C295BAECB0" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 12. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 7. Stenus circularis species group: ○ Stenus planifrons robustus; 8. Stenus clavicornis species group: ○ Stenus caspius, ● Stenus providus providus; 9. Stenus comma species group: ■ Stenus aereus, ○ Stenus asiaticus, ● Stenus bicornis, ▲ Stenus biguttatus, □ Stenus comma comma; 10. Stenus cordatus species group: ○ Stenus araxis, ● Stenus turk; 11. Stenus crassus and Stenus fornicatus species groups: ■ Stenus crassus, △ Stenus formicetorum, ○ Stenus fornicatus; 12. Stenus glacialis species group: ➕ Stenus armeniacus, ▲ Stenus hospes, ■ Stenus limicola, ○ Stenus medus, ▲ Stenus parcior, □ Stenus persicus, ● Stenus schah." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures7-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74429" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">9</figureCitation>
) are the first for the Iranian fauna and represent the easternmost known localities of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C941981AAFEAC2B71FF62A18A9C971A9" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph id="7CB21B1517BBBCE082B0F347F750DB20" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BFB59E387C8DC089EAEC651ECEA917BC" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Due to its distribution in the northeastern Mediterranean, 
<taxonomicName id="C4A56D8D2803363CD53DAC3871231764" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus bicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis id="0632C6BAEF8AFB53C7FACF3F90839D78" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Stenus bicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be regarded as a Pontomediterranean species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
